	<h1><a href="https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/wp_get_themes/">wp_get_themes ( <span class="arg-type">array</span>&nbsp;<span class="arg-name">$args</span>&nbsp;=&nbsp;<span class="arg-default">array()</span> )</a></h1>

	<section class="summary">
		<p>Returns an array of WP_Theme objects based on the arguments.</p>
	</section>


	<section class="description">
		<p>Despite advances over get_themes(), this function is quite expensive, and grows linearly with additional themes. Stick to wp_get_theme() if possible.</p>
	</section>

			<section class="return"><p><strong>Return:</strong> <span class='return-type'>(array)</span> Array of WP_Theme objects.</p></section>
	
